{{distinguish|Jukun Wapan language|Djugun language}} {{Infobox language |name = Jukun |altname = Jukun Takum |nativename=''Njikum'' |states = [[Cameroon]], [[Nigeria]] |region = |speakers = {{sigfig|2440|2}} in Cameroon |date=2000 |ref=e18 |speakers2=unknown number in Nigeria, but sufficient for significant L2 use<ref name=e18/> |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Benue–Congo languages|Benue–Congo]] |fam4= [[Jukunoid languages|Jukunoid]] |fam5= Central |fam6= Jukun languages |iso3=jbu |glotto=juku1254 |glottorefname=Jukun Takum }}
'''Jukun''' (''Njikum''), or more precisely '''Jukun Takum''', is a [[Jukunoid language]] of [[Cameroon]] used as a [[trade language]] in [[Nigeria]]. Though there are only a few thousand native speakers, and only a dozen in Nigeria (as of 2000), it is spoken as a second language in Nigeria by tens of thousands (40,000 reported in 1979).
The name ''Jukun'' is a cover term for several related Jukunoid languages, such as the much-more-numerous [[Wapan language|Jukun Wapan]].
