{{Infobox language |name=Jumli |region=[[Nepal]] |speakers=40,000 |date=2001 |ref=<ref name=e21>{{e21}}</ref> |script=[[Devanagari]] |familycolor=Indo-European |fam2=[[Indo-Iranian languages|Indo-Iranian]] |fam3=[[Indo-Aryan languages|Indo-Aryan]] |fam4=Northern |fam5=[[Eastern Pahari]] |iso3=jml |glotto=juml1238 |glottorefname=Jumli }}
'''Jumli''' is a language of [[Nepal]] closely related to [[Nepali language|Nepali]], and sometimes considered a dialect of it, though they are not close enough to understand complex discourse. Dialects include Chaudhabis, Sinja, Asi and Paanchsai.<ref name=e21></ref>
