{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2017}} {{Use Indian English|date=February 2017}} {{Infobox language |name=Kinnauri, Chitkuli |nativename=''Kanawaringskad'' |region=[[Himachal Pradesh]] |speakers={{sigfig|1060|4}} |date=2001 census<!--census for all Kinnauri lects--> |ref=<ref>{{e18|cik}}</ref><!--census for all Kinnauri lects--> |familycolor=Sino-Tibetan |fam2=[[Tibeto-Kanauri languages|Tibeto-Kanauri]] ? |fam3=[[West Himalayish languages|West Himalayish]] |fam4=Kanauri |dia1= |lc1=cik |ld1=Chitkuli Kinnauri |glotto=chit1279 |glottorefname=Kinnauric |notice=IPA }}
'''Chitkuli Kinnauri''' is a language spoken in Kinnaur district of Himachal Pradesh, India Page text.<ref>[[Kinnaur district]], additional text.</ref> It is spoken in two villages in Sangla districts of Kinnaur - Chitkul and Rakchham villages. It is classified under Sino-Tibetan, Tibeto-Burman, Western Tibeto-Burman, Bodish, West Himalayish, Kinauri Page text.<ref>[http://www.ethnologue.com/language/cik], additional text.</ref> The number of speakers as per Ethnologue (data is from a survey) is 1060 in 1998.<ref>[http://www.ethnologue.com/language/cik], additional text.</ref>
