The '''Ossetian Wikipedia''' ({{lang-os|{{#property:P1448}}}}) is the [[Ossetian language|Ossetian-language]] edition of the free online encyclopedia [[Wikipedia]]. It was created on 28 February 2005.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Соколова|first1=Наталья|title=Википедия на осетинском языке открыта!|url=http://www.iriston.ru/ru/news.php?nid=396|website=iriston.ru|accessdate=4 May 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111216210346/http://www.iriston.ru/ru/news.php?nid=396|archivedate=16 December 2011|language=Russian|date=28 February 2005}}</ref><ref name="Creation">{{cite web|last=Zachte|first=Erik|title=Creation history / Accomplishments|url=http://stats.wikimedia.org/EN/TablesWikipediaGrowthSummary.htm|work=stats.wikimedia.org|accessdate=10 April 2013}}</ref> With approximately {{formatnum:{{#expr:{{NUMBEROF|ARTICLES|os}} round -3}}}} articles, it is currently the {{Ordinal|{{Wikipedia rank by size|os}}}}-largest Wikipedia as measured by the number of articles.<ref name="wmeta">{{cite web|title=List of Wikipedias|url=http://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/List_of_Wikipedias#1000.2B_articles|work=Meta-Wiki|publisher=Wikimedia Foundation|accessdate={{CURRENTDAY}} {{CURRENTMONTHNAME}} {{CURRENTYEAR}}}}</ref> Since its creation, the Ossetian Wikipedia has been called "what is perhaps the only website written entirely in Ossetian."<ref>{{cite news|last1=ИВАНОВ|first1=Вячеслав|title=НК № 4. Электронная энциклопедия по-осетински|url=http://www.caucasus-news.ru/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=494&Itemid=1|accessdate=4 May 2015|date=28 February 2005|language=Russian}}</ref>

On 3 March 2010, the Ossetian Wikipedia made headlines in local newspapers for reaching a double milestone. The edition was 5 years old and had just passed the 5000 articles threshold.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Ревазова|first1=Д.|title=Энциклопедия на осетинском в Интернете весьма популярна|journal=Северная Осетия|date=3 March 2010|url=http://amikeco.ru/wp-content/uploads/gazeta.pdf|accessdate=4 May 2015|language=Russian}}</ref>

